com.googlecode.sarasvati
Interface Env

All Known Implementing Classes:
MapEnv, NestedEnv
public interface Env

An Env is a container for variables. The variables are likely all stored as strings, to allow simple database storage, but they may be retrieved and set as strings, longs and booleans for convenience.

Author:
Paul Lorenz
